o-quit-mamata-banerjee-led-party%2Farticleshow%2F108199016.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Veteran%20TMC%20leader%20Tapas%20Roy%20hinted%20at%20quitting%20the%20Mamata%20Banerjee-led%20party%20due%20to%20displeasure%20over%20its%20functioning%2C%20handling%20of%20the%20Sandeshkhali%20issue%2C%20lack%20of%20support%20during%20his%20residence%20raid%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%2C%20and%20corruption%20allegations.%20He%20is%20expected%20to%20resign%20as%20TMC%20MLA%20today%20afternoon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20CITY%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkolkata%2Fsenior-tmc-mla-tapas-roy-likely-to-quit-mamata-banerjee-led-party%2Farticleshow%2F108199016.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20How%20Supreme%20Court%20Removed%20Immunity%20To%20MPs%2FMLAs%20In%20Bribery%20Cases%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20landmark%20verdict%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20ruled%20that%20an%20MP%20or%20MLA%20cannot%20claim%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20if%20he%2Fshe%20is%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20for%20a%20vote%20or%20a%20speech%20in%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20by%20the%20seven-judge%20Constitution%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20explained%20in%20the%20judgment%20why%20the%20legal%20shield%20provided%20to%20lawmakers%20will%20not%20protect%20them%20in%20cases%20of%20bribery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20Immunity%20for%20Lawmakers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticles%20105%20and%20194%20of%20the%20Constitution%20protect%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20from%20prosecution%20to%20enable%20them%20to%20work%20without%20the%20fear%20of%20legal%20action%20against%20them.%20These%20provisions%20provide%20them%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20protect%20them%20from%20being%20prosecuted%20for%20their%20remarks%20in%20the%20House%20or%20any%20vote%20in%20Parliament%20or%20a%20House%20committee%20he%2Fshe%20may%20be%20part%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20an%20MP%20or%20an%20MLA%20cannot%20face%20a%20defamation%20case%20for%20any%20remark%20made%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House.%20If%20a%20lawmaker%20makes%20an%20objectionable%20remark%2C%20the%20Speaker%20-%20and%20not%20courts%20-%20will%20take%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%201998%20Judgment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday's%20verdict%20set%20aside%20the%201998%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20case.%20In%20July%201993%2C%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20against%20the%20minority%20government%20led%20by%20the%20former%20Prime%20Minister.%20His%20government%20had%20survived%20with%20a%20slim%20margin%20-%20265%20votes%20in%20favour%20and%20251%20against.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20allegations%20surfaced%20that%20legislators%20of%20Jharkhand%20Mukti%20Morcha%20had%20taken%20bribes%20to%20vote%20in%20support%20of%20the%20government.%20In%20the%201998%20ruling%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20with%20a%203%3A2%20majority%20that%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20were%20immune%20from%20prosecution%20in%20bribery%20cases%20for%20their%20vote%20provided%20they%20kept%20their%20side%20of%20the%20bargain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Court%20Said%20Today%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20held%20that%20taking%20a%20bribe%20is%20an%20independent%20crime%20and%20it%20has%20no%20link%20with%20what%20a%20lawmaker%20says%20or%20does%20inside%20the%20Parliament%20or%20legislative%20assembly.%20Hence%2C%20the%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20enjoyed%20by%20lawmakers%20will%20not%20shield%20them.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20protection%20granted%20under%20Articles%20105%20and%20194%20cannot%20protect%20lawmakers%20in%20bribery%20cases%20because%20they%20have%20no%20link%20with%20their%20duties%20as%20members%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20warned%20that%20such%20protection%20would%20create%20a%20section%20that%20can%20enjoy%20unregulated%20exemption%20from%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20corruption%20and%20bribery%20by%20legislators%20can%20potentially%20destroy%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20Indian%20Parliamentary%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20105%2C%20it%20said%2C%20is%20aimed%20at%20maintaining%20a%20conducive%20environment%20for%20discussions.%20When%20a%20member%20takes%20a%20bribe%20for%20a%20speech%2C%20this%20environment%20is%20disrupted%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EComments%20On%20the%201998%20Verdict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelivering%20the%20unanimous%20verdict%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20disagree%20with%20the%20judgment%20in%20PV%20Narasimha%20(case).%20The%20judgment%20in%20that%20case%20which%20granted%20immunity%20to%20legislators%20for%20taking%20bribes%20to%20cast%20votes%20has%20wide%20ramifications%20and%20is%20overruled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20that%20the%201998%20judgment%20results%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bparadoxical%20situation%26quot%3B%20where%20a%20legislator%20who%20accepts%20a%20bribe%20and%20votes%20accordingly%20is%20protected%2C%20and%20a%20legislator%20who%2C%20despite%20taking%20a%20bribe%2C%20votes%20independently%20is%20prosecuted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20This%20Verdict%20Means%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20several%20decades%2C%20cash-for-votes%20trading%20has%20been%20a%20massive%20challenge%20in%20preserving%20the%20sanctity%20of%20electoral%20mandates.%20Prior%20to%20today's%20judgment%2C%20no%20MP%20or%20MLA%20could%20be%20prosecuted%20if%20they%20took%20a%20bribe%20and%20cast%20their%20vote%20accordingly.%20But%20now%20they%20have%20lost%20this%20immunity.%20The%20court%20held%20that%20the%20crime%20was%20complete%20the%20moment%20a%20lawmaker%20accepted%20the%20bribe%2C%20and%20the%20immunity%20he%2Fshe%20enjoys%20inside%20the%20House%20won't%20provide%20protection%20in%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709538300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fc1l320oo_supreme-court-ani_625x300_23_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-explained-how-supreme-court-stripped-mps-mlas-of-immunity-in-bribery-cases-5173098%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20landmark%20verdict%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20ruled%20that%20an%20MP%20or%20MLA%20cannot%20claim%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20if%20he%2Fshe%20is%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20for%20a%20vote%20or%20a%20speech%20in%20the%20House.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-explained-how-supreme-court-stripped-mps-mlas-of-immunity-in-bribery-cases-5173098%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Austin%20Butler's%20surprise%20kiss%20in%20Dune%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709538263000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108199286%2Cimgsize-32792.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Faustin-butlers-surprise-kiss-in-dune-part-two-was-improvised%2Farticleshow%2F108199326.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108199326.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EButler%20explained%20that%20his%20decision%20to%20improvise%20the%20kiss%20was%20to%20elicit%20a%20genuine%20reaction%20from%20Skarsg%C3%A5rd%2C%20highlighting%20how%20acting%20is%20all%20about%20affecting%20someone%20else.%20In%20the%20movie%2C%20Butler's%20character%2C%20Feyd-Rautha%2C%20serves%20as%20a%20villain%20pitted%20against%20Timoth%C3%A9e%20Chalamet's%20Paul%20Atreidies%20and%20his%20uncle%2C%20Vladimir%20Harkonnen%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Faustin-butlers-surprise-kiss-in-dune-part-two-was-improvised%2Farticleshow%2F108199326.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20City%20Is%20Just%20Months%20Away%20From%20Running%20Out%20Of%20Water%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMexico%20City%2C%20a%20sprawling%20metropolis%20of%20nearly%2022%20million%20people%20and%20counted%20among%20the%20world's%20largest%20cities%2C%20grapples%20with%20a%20dire%20water%20crisis.%20A%20complex%20web%20of%20issues%2C%20including%20geographical%20challenges%2C%20disorderly%20urban%20expansion%2C%20and%20ageing%20infrastructure%20prone%20to%20leaks%2C%20is%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20effects%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYears%20of%20deficient%20rainfall%2C%20extended%20droughts%2C%20and%20rising%20temperatures%20have%20exacerbated%20the%20strain%20on%20an%20already%20overburdened%20water%20system%2C%20prompting%20authorities%20to%20impose%20substantial%20limitations%20on%20water%20extraction%20from%20reservoirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSeveral%20neighbourhoods%20have%20suffered%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20water%20for%20weeks%2C%20and%20there%20are%20still%20four%20months%20left%20for%20the%20rains%20to%20start%2C%26quot%3B%20Christian%20Dominguez%20Sarmiento%2C%20an%20atmospheric%20scientist%20at%20the%20National%20Autonomous%20University%20of%20Mexico%20(UNAM)%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F25%2Fclimate%2Fmexico-city-water-crisis-climate-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20city's%20vulnerability%20is%20deeply%20rooted%20in%20its%20historical%20development.%20Constructed%20on%20a%20high-altitude%20former%20lakebed%2C%20Mexico%20City%20(elevation%3A%20approximately%207%2C300%20ft)%20faces%20ongoing%20challenges%20such%20as%20subsidence%20due%20to%20its%20clay-rich%20soil%2C%20seismic%20vulnerabilities%2C%20and%20heightened%20susceptibility%20to%20climate%20change.%20Urban%20expansion%20has%20transformed%20its%20natural%20landscape%2C%20replacing%20wetlands%20and%20rivers%20with%20concrete%20and%20asphalt%2C%20exacerbating%20seasonal%20extremes%20of%20flooding%20and%20drought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMexico%20City%20relies%20heavily%20on%20its%20overexploited%20aquifer%2C%20which%20provides%20roughly%2060%25%20of%20its%20water%20but%20also%20contributes%20to%20the%20city's%20alarming%20subsidence%20rate%20of%2020%20inches%20annually.%20This%20overreliance%2C%20combined%20with%20urban%20expansion%20that%20replaced%20natural%20landscapes%20with%20concrete%20and%20asphalt%2C%20exacerbates%20seasonal%20extremes%20of%20flooding%20and%20drought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20February%20report%20reveals%20that%20nearly%2090%25%20of%20the%20city%20faces%20severe%20drought%20conditions%2C%20reflecting%20the%20broader%20situation%20where%2060%25%20of%20the%20nation%20experiences%20moderate%20to%20exceptional%20drought.%20This%20vulnerability%20is%20amplified%20by%20Mexico's%20sensitivity%20to%20natural%20climate%20fluctuations.%20La%20Nina%20events%20exacerbate%20droughts%2C%20while%20El%20Nino%20disrupts%20regular%20rainy%20seasons%2C%20leaving%20the%20city's%20water%20resources%20constantly%20under%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impending%20water%20crisis%20fuels%20concerns%20regarding%20a%20potential%20%26quot%3Bday%20zero%26quot%3B%20scenario.%20This%20critical%20juncture%20would%20signify%20the%20Cutzamala%20system's%20critically%20low%20water%20levels%2C%20rendering%20it%20incapable%20of%20meeting%20the%20city's%20essential%20water%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709538180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2