h%20had%20upheld%20the%20immunity%20for%20lawmakers%20in%20cases%20where%20MPs%20or%20MLAs%20take%20bribes%20for%20a%20speech%20or%20a%20vote%20in%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBribery%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20is%20not%20protected%20by%20parliamentary%20privileges%20and%20the%20interpretation%20of%20the%201998%20verdict%20is%20contrary%20to%20Articles%20105%20and%20194%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20These%20two%20Articles%20provide%20elected%20representatives%20legal%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20to%20enable%20them%20to%20work%20without%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20disagree%20with%20the%20judgment%20in%20PV%20Narasimha%20(case).%20The%20judgment%20in%20that%20case%20which%20granted%20immunity%20to%20legislators%20for%20taking%20bribes%20to%20cast%20votes%20has%20wide%20ramifications%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20case%20had%20come%20up%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20against%20his%20government%20in%20July%201993.%20The%20minority%20government%20had%20survived%20with%20a%20slim%20margin%20-%20265%20votes%20in%20favour%20and%20251%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20however%2C%20a%20scandal%20emerged%20and%20allegations%20surfaced%20that%20legislators%20of%20Jharkhand%20Mukti%20Morcha%20had%20taken%20bribes%20to%20vote%20in%20support%20of%20the%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20government.%20In%201998%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20the%20lawmakers'%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20extended%20to%20their%20votes%20and%20speeches%20inside%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20today%20said%20a%20claim%20for%20immunity%20in%20such%20situations%20fails%20to%20pass%20the%20test%20of%20being%20necessary%20to%20discharge%20legislative%20functions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20hold%20that%20bribery%20is%20not%20protected%20by%20Parliamentary%20privileges.%20Corruption%20and%20bribery%20by%20legislators%20destroy%20the%20functioning%20of%20Indian%20Parliamentary%20democracy.%20An%20MLA%20taking%20a%20bribe%20to%20vote%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20elections%20is%20also%20liable%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PV%20Narasimha%20judgment%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said%2C%20results%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bparadoxical%20situation%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20a%20legislator%20who%20accepts%20a%20bribe%20and%20votes%20accordingly%20is%20protected%20whereas%20a%20legislator%20who%20votes%20independently%20despite%20taking%20a%20bribe%20is%20prosecuted.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709537460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fq30ss1g_supreme-court_650x400_04_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-immunity-to-mlas-and-mps-in-bribery-cases-rules-supreme-court-5172351%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lawmakers%20in%20parliament%20and%20state%20legislatures%20are%20not%20immune%20from%20prosecution%20in%20bribery%20cases%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20today.%20The%20landmark%20verdict%20was%20delivered%20by%20a%20seven-judge%20constitution%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-immunity-to-mlas-and-mps-in-bribery-cases-rules-supreme-court-5172351%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-immunity-to-mlas-and-mps-in-bribery-cases-rules-supreme-court-5172351%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-immunity-to-mlas-and-mps-in-bribery-cases-rules-supreme-court-5172351%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dune%202%20earns%20Rs%2011.25%20crore%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709537400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108198915%2Cimgsiz