ity%20fails%20to%20fulfill%20the%20test%20of%20whether%20such%20immunity%20is%20necessary%20to%20discharge%20legislative%20functions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBribery%20is%20not%20rendered%20immune%20under%20Article%20105%20or%20194%20because%20a%20legislator%20indulging%20in%20bribery%20commits%20a%20criminal%20act%20that%20is%20not%20essential%20for%20the%20function%20of%20casting%20a%20vote%20or%20giving%20a%20speech.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20offence%20of%20bribery%20does%20not%20depend%20on%20whether%20the%20vote%20or%20speech%20is%20given%20later.%20The%20offence%20is%20complete%20at%20the%20point%20in%20time%20when%20the%20legislator%20accepts%20a%20bribe.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBribery%20isn't%20protected%20by%20parliamentary%20privileges.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20interpretation%20of%20the%201998%20verdict%20is%20contrary%20to%20the%20Constitution's%20Articles%20105%20and%20194.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20purpose%20and%20object%20of%20legislative%20privileges%20must%20be%20borne%20in%20mind.%20Privileges%20are%20for%20the%20house%20collectively.%20Articles%20105%2F194%20seek%20to%20create%20a%20fearless%20environment%20for%20the%20members.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECorruption%20and%20bribery%20by%20legislators%20destroy%20the%20functioning%20of%20Indian%20Parliamentary%20democracy.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20judgment%20results%20in%20a%20paradoxical%20situation%20where%20a%20legislator%20who%20accepts%20a%20bribe%20and%20votes%20accordingly%20is%20protected%2C%20whereas%20a%20legislator%20who%2C%20despite%20taking%20a%20bribe%2C%20votes%20independently%20is%20prosecuted.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMLA%20taking%20a%20bribe%20to%20vote%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20elections%20is%20also%20liable%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709533260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fuqrqrqg8_justice-dy-chandrachud-ani-_625x300_03_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%