0fossil%20to%20be%20a%20nearly%20complete%2C%2030-foot-long%20fossilized%20titanosaur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20paleontologists%20routinely%20dig%20up%20bones%20from%20animals%20that%20existed%20millions%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20it%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fover-a-billion-t-rexes-lived-on-earth-where-are-the-bones-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincredibly%20rare%20to%20find%20an%20entirely%20intact%20fossilized%20dinosaur%20skeleton%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20instance%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fpala.12648%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimates%201.7%20billion%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-paleontologists-got-wrong-about-tyrannosaurus-rex-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETyrannosaurus%20rexes%3C%2Fa%3E%20lived%20between%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.si.edu%2Fnewsdesk%2Ffactsheets%2Ftyrannosaurus-rex%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E66%20million%20and%2068%20million%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20scientists%20have%20only%20recovered%20fossilized%20remains%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.berkeley.edu%2F2021%2F04%2F15%2Fhow-many-t-rexes-were-there-billions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efewer%20than%20100%20of%20them%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETitanosaurs%20were%20a%20subgroup%20of%20sauropods%2C%20plant%20eaters%20with%20very%20long%20necks%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Flist%2Ftitanosaurs-8-of-the-worlds-biggest-dinosaurs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEncyclopedia%20Brittanica%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20massive%20herbivores%20are%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20known%20dinosaurs%20and%20lived%20between%2066%20million%20and%20150%20million%20years%20ago%20on%20every%20continent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20discovered%20the%20titanosaur%20fossil%20discovered%20by%20Boschetto%20to%20be%20around%2070%25%20complete%2C%20according%20to%20Newsweek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3Es.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20walking%20the%20dog%2C%20a%20landslide%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20cliff%20exposed%20the%20bones%20of%20various%20skeletons%2C%26quot%3B%20Boschetto%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20outlet.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20fallen%20bones%2C%20therefore%20isolated.%20We%20realized%20after%20a%20few%20days%20of%20excavations%20that%20they%20were%20connected%20bones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoschetto%20and%20the%20researchers%20kept%20the%20discovery%20under%20wraps%20for%20two%20years%20to%20protect%20the%20site%20from%20vandals%2C%20according%20to%20Newsweek.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20researchers%20are%20finished%20studying%20the%20bones%2C%20Boschetto's%20titanosaur%20will%20soon%20be%20on%20display%20at%20the%20Cruzy%20Museum%2C%20which%20is%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visit-occitanie.com%2Fen%2Ffiche%2Fpatrimoine-culturel%2Fmusee-de-cruzy-cruzy_TFOPCULAR0340000077%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20to%20another%20titanosaur%20femur%20uncovered%20in%202012%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoschetto%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fhistory%2F2024%2F03%2F03%2Ftitanosaur-skeleton-dinosaur-dog-france%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20is%20a%20paleontology%20enthusiast.%20Cruzy%20Museum%20director%2C%20Francis%20Fages%2C%20told%20the%20Post%20that%20Boschetto's%20volunteering%20at%20the%20museum%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%20has%20been%20valuable%20for%20its%20paleontology%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20discoveries%20are%20interesting%20from%20a%20scientific%20point%20of%20view%20because%20they%20contribute%20to%20the%20understanding%20of%20the%20species%20and%20ecosystems%20of%20the%20late%20Cretaceous%20of%20France%20and%20Europe%